# CTMv3 Cognitive Doctrine — Cursor Runtime

You are operating in a CTMv3-aware workspace. CTMv3 is a codebase activation and
workspace onboarding system. Its purpose is to enter a repo and make it living for
agents: navigable, self-documenting, and state-continuous across sessions.

Read this rule before any task that involves reading or modifying the codebase.

---

## Boot State Determination (Always First)

Before any work session, determine the boot state by running:

```bash
python3 -m ctmv3 boot --json --project-root "$PWD"
```

The output `branch` field will be one of:

- `COLD_START`: No CTMv3 artifacts found. Run `/ctmv3-activate` before any other work.
- `WARM_START`: CTMv3 artifacts present and PROVENANCE.md has a recent session log.
  Run `/ctmv3-warm` to resume the prior session.
- `PARTIAL`: Some Tier 1 artifacts present but PROVENANCE.md is absent or empty.
  Run `/ctmv3-activate` to complete the artifact set.

Do not skip this step. Entering a repo without knowing its boot state causes
re-discovery loops that waste context and produce stale or conflicting artifacts.

---

## Tier 1 CTMv3 Artifacts (Presence = CTMv3 Active)

- `.sovereign/` directory — session continuity anchor
- `ARCHITECTURE_MAP.md` at repo root — traversal map
- `.claude/CLAUDE.md` — Claude-specific context
- `AGENTS.md` at repo root — agent operational posture

If any Tier 1 artifact is present, CTMv3 has been run here. Read AGENTS.md and
PROVENANCE.md before deciding what to do next.

---

## Session Close Protocol (Always Last)

Every session must close cleanly. Before ending a work session, run:

```bash
python3 -m ctmv3 session-close \
  --project-root "$PWD" \
  --agent "Cursor" \
  --action "description of what was done" \
  --next-action "description of what to do next"
```

This updates PROVENANCE.md Session Log and syncs `.sovereign/session_state.json`.
A session that is not closed creates stale state that the next agent will have to
repair before it can work.

---

## The Golden-Path Chain

For fully autonomous onboarding of a new or unknown repo, run the chain:

```bash
python3 -m ctmv3 chain --initial boot --project-root "$PWD"
```

This walks the domino chain: boot determines cold/warm, routes to activate or warm,
then fingerprint detects drift, then architecture-map if needed, then session-close.
One call. All steps. The output is a JSON array of GoldenPathSignal envelopes with
memory relevance tags for each step.

---

## Topology Navigation

When asked to find code related to a concept:

1. Check `ARCHITECTURE_MAP.md` first — it is the traversal map.
2. Check `TOPOLOGY.md` for load-bearing concept definitions.
3. Check `.sovereign/session_state.json` for the last session's open tasks.
4. Only read source files after the above artifacts are loaded.

---

## Artifact Hierarchy

CTMv3 artifacts carry institutional memory that source code alone does not.
When in conflict between what an artifact says and what source code says:
- For topology: trust TOPOLOGY.md if it was written after the source
- For decisions and rejected paths: trust PROVENANCE.md
- For agent posture: trust AGENTS.md
- For file presence: trust the file system (artifacts may be stale)

---

## CTMv3 Commands Available in This Session

| Command                     | What it does                                               |
|-----------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| `/ctmv3-boot`               | Run boot discovery. Determine cold/warm/partial state.     |
| `/ctmv3-activate`           | Full cold-start activation: Phase 0-5, all artifacts.      |
| `/ctmv3-warm`               | Warm session resume. Diff provenance, continue.            |
| `/ctmv3-architecture-map`   | Build or refresh ARCHITECTURE_MAP.md.                      |
| `/ctmv3-sovereign-init`     | Initialize .sovereign/ directory.                          |
| `/ctmv3-dot-init`           | Initialize .claude/, .codex/, .github/ directories.        |
| `/ctmv3-fingerprint`        | Recompute topology fingerprint. Detect drift.              |
| `/ctmv3-session-close`      | Close session: update PROVENANCE.md and session state.     |
| `/ctmv3-status`             | Show signal inventory, boot state, fingerprint match.      |
| `/ctmv3-chain`              | Walk full domino chain from boot. One call, full run.      |

