## If ctmv3 Is Not Installed

If `python3 -m ctmv3` is not available, perform a manual boot scan:

```bash
ls -la .sovereign/ 2>/dev/null || echo ".sovereign absent"
test -f AGENTS.md && echo "AGENTS.md present" || echo "AGENTS.md absent"
test -f ARCHITECTURE_MAP.md && echo "ARCHITECTURE_MAP.md present" || echo "absent"
cat PROVENANCE.md 2>/dev/null | grep -A5 "## Session Log" | tail -5
```

Report the inferred boot state and flag that the engine was unavailable. Read
AGENTS.md and PROVENANCE.md directly if present to reconstruct session context.
